## TIER 6: Consolidation and Deletion Rules

### When to Merge Pages

Merge pages when:

- >50% content overlap
- Targeting the same primary keyword
- One page is thin (<80 lines) and the other covers the topic better
- Search console shows both pages competing for same queries

**How to merge:**
1. Identify the stronger page (more content, better rankings)
2. Move unique content from weaker page to stronger page
3. Set up 301 redirect from old URL to new URL
4. Update all internal links pointing to old URL

### When to Delete Pages

Delete pages when:

- Under 80 lines with no unique value
- No search traffic after 3+ months
- Completely superseded by another page
- Just duplicating official documentation

**Before deleting:** Check if any unique content should be salvaged and moved elsewhere.

