## Quality Checklist: Before Every Publish

Run this checklist before pushing any content to WordPress:

- [ ] **Search query identified** — Can state the exact query this targets
- [ ] **Intent matched** — Content answers what the searcher wants
- [ ] **Depth achieved** — Meets minimum line count for page type
- [ ] **Substantive content** — Has code, tables, or practical guidance (not just template)
- [ ] **No duplication** — Doesn't cannibalize existing pages
- [ ] **SEO meta complete** — seo_title (<60 chars), seo_description (<155 chars)
- [ ] **Internal links** — Links to 3-5 related pages, will be linked from 2+ pages
- [ ] **FAQ complete** — 5+ questions including "Is this tool free?"
- [ ] **Better than competitors** — Can articulate why this beats Google result #1

**If any checkbox fails, do not publish. Fix it first or reconsider whether this page should exist.**
